  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Wow, there's a lot of changes here. Some detailed feedback:

ktarnowski, do you want to take a look in terms of spacing?

Re-organizing the page this way exposes some of the problems with the site.
Maybe we can focus next month on "performance and basic improvements"...? Who knows.

Some things that came to mind:

* You point to the somewhat useless /+projects/ page. I guess that's the best
place to point, but maaan, that sure exposes the flaws with that page. You
should keep it that way, and we should fix /+projects/. (I kind of wonder if you
should link to a sample project page instead... but which one? Probably not
OpenHatch because that would be confusing.)

On the "Attract contributors..." side, I would suggest adding a box labeled:
"Create a profile to talk about your involvement" and linking somewhere. Where
to link? If you want to link to a sample profile, someone like willkg's profile
would be good.

There's some sense in which the text could use some sprucing up to really
suggest activity. Maybe linking to examples would help with that, but I don't
want to clutter everything up.

I wish that "Tell people who have clicked your project's 'I want to help' button
how they can contribute" could link to the projects that the person actually
works on. But I guess the user is not logged in yet.

You wrote "volunteer opportunities finder" but in e.g.
<a href="https://openhatch.org/about/">https://openhatch.org/about/</a> we call it "volunteer opportunity finder".

It looks really really good, as per the mockup. Also I really like how you
explain what bitesize means in "bitesize (easy)" on the "Contribute to..." view.

running low on power</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
