  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I have a couple of suggestions regarding the design's:

* [ALL] Adding vertical space between elements should improve the general look 
and feel of the site. In particular between top navigation bar and OH tagline, OH 
tagline and tab widget, tab caption and its contents.

* [ALL] I think that the tabbed widget would look better with small border/rim 
around it, like 'Recent activity' or 'OpenHatch news' boxes. Right now it
s too bright.

* [ALL] Additionally to the above, adding small border/rim around the active tab 
itself might look really nice. Applying rounded corners might help as well.

* [MOCKUP-3] Adding some padding (yo!) between section header and border-bottom 
might look better. Try changing the color of the border-bottom to something from 
#888 - #eee.

* [MOCKUP-3] Recommended people section. Try to organize entries as follows:
  
         Width: ~50%   Some padding (&gt;20px?)             The rest
              |              |               /--------------/
  /-----------------------\/---\/-----------------------\
  [Avatar] [Name] [Surname]     [Projects]
           [Nickname]           [Tags]
           [City]
           [Country]

In general, I like the way in which the design is heading. Good job!</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
