  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Are you okay with iterating on this once every two-ish months? I think it makes
sense to focus the current design work on exposing the currently-good
functionality. I also think it's okay to not try really hard to expose the profile.

I think that the "Make your first contribution" and "Make your nth contribution"
are the same right now; even non-newbies could use training missions in e.g.
version control tools they don't know. Maybe call that heading "Make a
contribution to open source".

I think that "Attract contributors to your project" feels pretty fleshed-out, too.

I would be okay with skipping the "Help out" section for now, since it's kind of
weak. That's what I mean by iterating -- one day, maybe we'll have features that
make sense to fill up a section. But I actually do think that if we show people
how to help join/drive the OpenHatch project itself, then we'd have enough meat
there to justify a section. I think it would be a useful section, too. Plus we
can link people to the Events list.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg1045">msg1045 (view)</a></th>
