  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I guess 'Help others' could be subsumed under 'Attract contributors to your
project', though the implicit idea that people would be only interested in
mentoring so as to get people to work on their favored project seems a little
mercenary (if common).

'Profile' could be left out if the workflow for the rest of the site made it
eminently clear that bothering to fill the profile out makes using the rest of
the features possible/easier...

Anyway, I'd like to get this schema mostly hammered out before doing
mockups/actual redesigning... Seems like the more sensible order to do things.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg1044">msg1044 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: aldeka</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-02-12.22:49:11</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>To me, it seems like there's more like five segments of needs / activities that
we could have tabs for:

* Make your first contribution
** Missions
** Find a mentor
** Project page Q&amp;As
** Volopps

* Make your nth contribution
** Project page Q&amp;As
** Volopps
** Events/organize a local hack session (via /+people/ (someday (?)))

* Attract contributors to your project
** Add info to your project page
** 'I wanna help' button
** Buildhelper (someday)
** Forums (someday)

* Help others
** Edit proj pages for projects you contribute to
** Project forums (someday)
** Mentoring

* Show off what you've done
** Profile

The last of these is pretty undeveloped, and some of the others rely rather
heavily on features that don't exist yet.

Is there any way to combine these under a heading that actually makes sense? If
we e.g. didn't have the profile listed or linked under any tab, would that be
okay or terrible?</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg1027">msg1027 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: aldeka</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-02-12.21:33:05</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Through tabs at the top, you should be able to switch between these modes at will.

   1. "Make your first contribution" # (though how do we make this inclusive to
people who *have* contributed before?)
   2. "Attract contributors to your project"
   3. "Help make this website better" 

Each mode has information / a dashboard associated with it, e.g. "Attract
contributors" would have "X new people clicked the 'I wanna help' button! Go
here to respond..."

Arguably these modes should be thematically consistent between the logged-in and
not-logged-in versions of the landing page (the former just has personalized
data e.g. recommended bugs).

Of course, the proposed schema leaves out some things that are currently
featured on the home page, mainly "Tell your open source story". Is there a way
to include that feature in this schema? Or is it not worth featuring?

Also, do we really want to elevate OH dev to that level of prominence?</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
